To set up a payment system in YouTube, you actually don’t get paid directly from YouTube. 
You earn money through Google AdSense, which is connected to your YouTube channel.

Here’s the complete step-by-step process:

✅ Step 1: Meet YouTube Monetization Requirements
Before setting payment, your channel must join the YouTube Partner Program (YPP):

You need:
1,000 subscribers
4,000 watch hours (last 12 months) OR 10 million Shorts views (90 days)
Follow YouTube policies
Enable 2-Step Verification on Google account

✅ Step 2: Enable Monetization
Go to YouTube Studio: https://studio.youtube.com
Click Earn (left menu)
Click Apply for YPP
Accept terms and connect your channel

✅ Step 3: Create Google AdSense Account (Payment System)
In YouTube Studio → Earn section
Click Set up AdSense
Sign in or create a new AdSense account
Fill in:
Name (must match your bank account)
Address (very important for PIN verification)
Phone number
Email

✅ Step 4: Link YouTube with AdSense
After approval, your YouTube channel will be linked automatically to AdSense
This is where your earnings will be stored

✅ Step 5: Add Payment Method (Bank Setup)

Once AdSense is approved:

Go to AdSense Dashboard
Click Payments → Payment Methods
Add:
Bank account (recommended in Bangladesh)
OR Western Union (in some cases)

You must enter:

Bank name
Account holder name
Account number
SWIFT/BIC code

✅ Step 6: Verify Address (PIN Code)
When you earn around $10, Google sends a PIN by post mail
Enter that PIN in AdSense to activate payments

💰 When Do You Get Paid?
Minimum payout threshold: $100
Payment date: Usually 21–26 of each month

⚠️ Important Tips
Use real name and real address (very important)
Do not use fake clicks or bots
Make sure bank details match AdSense name

